1
00:00:00,920 --> 00:00:03,160
I'll go do the final venue check

2
00:00:03,450 --> 00:00:04,690
I'll come get you later.

3
00:00:04,690 --> 00:00:05,490
Noted.

4
00:00:11,870 --> 00:00:12,630
Come in.

5
00:00:14,070 --> 00:00:17,030
Yaho.. Brother.

6
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:19,780
What a surprise

7
00:00:19,980 --> 00:00:22,130
I'm having my book signing here tomorrow, too.

8
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:24,520
You're not copying me, are you?

9
00:00:25,470 --> 00:00:27,590
Showing up the day before the event.

10
00:00:27,950 --> 00:00:29,390
You seem quite free.

11
00:00:30,110 --> 00:00:31,160
Really.

12
00:00:31,300 --> 00:00:32,310
That's so mean

13
00:00:32,510 --> 00:00:35,250
I specially came to say hi during recon.

14
00:00:36,860 --> 00:00:39,110
Sign my book when I buy it later.

15
00:00:39,960 --> 00:00:41,200
I didn't ask you to sit.

16
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:43,550
Not saying "please sit" is rude.

17
00:00:44,230 --> 00:00:45,710
But it can't be helped.

18
00:00:45,960 --> 00:00:47,370
Given your upbringing.

19
00:00:48,410 --> 00:00:50,030
Is that the only line you've got?

20
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:52,850
Heartless father.

21
00:00:52,970 --> 00:00:55,500
Man-buying mother, and me craving love.

22
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:57,820
Aren't you tired of that yet?

23
00:00:58,370 --> 00:00:59,610
You're also a writer.

24
00:00:59,890 --> 00:01:01,810
Come up with some newer material.

25
00:01:02,660 --> 00:01:03,520
Hmm...

26
00:01:04,020 --> 00:01:05,140
You are right about that.

27
00:01:07,130 --> 00:01:11,210
Your family's collapse is well-known.

28
00:01:14,290 --> 00:01:15,180
So then...

29
00:01:15,940 --> 00:01:19,450
The son of a man-buying mother

30
00:01:19,460 --> 00:01:21,100
grows up to buy young men, too?

31
00:01:22,790 --> 00:01:25,880
Someone bought with money could never love you.

32
00:01:27,340 --> 00:01:28,050
Oh my?

33
00:01:28,830 --> 00:01:30,050
Did I hit a nerve?

34
00:01:30,650 --> 00:01:31,760
If you're done talking...

35
00:01:31,860 --> 00:01:32,860
Not yet.

36
00:01:34,090 --> 00:01:34,700
Let's be real.

37
00:01:34,710 --> 00:01:36,550
It's just an obsessive father complex.

38
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:38,100
Seeking comfort from men.

39
00:01:38,650 --> 00:01:42,550
In the end, the son gets abandoned, too.

40
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:44,590
How about an ending
where he gets dumped and goes insane?

41
00:01:45,290 --> 00:01:47,240
Ai Rakumoto's signature.

42
00:01:47,580 --> 00:01:50,350
Ultra-miserable romantic tragedy.

43
00:01:52,450 --> 00:01:53,270
Rejected.

44
00:01:54,610 --> 00:01:56,800
If you want me to lose my temper
and throw water on you.

45
00:01:57,370 --> 00:01:58,810
Think a bit harder.

46
00:01:59,750 --> 00:02:00,870
I agree.

47
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:02,100
What?

48
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:04,150
Are you grabbing my hand and force me to splash you?

49
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:07,070
No.

50
00:02:09,290 --> 00:02:10,830
This way...

51
00:02:11,460 --> 00:02:12,660
is much simpler.

52
00:02:27,070 --> 00:02:28,560
What happened?

53
00:02:28,620 --> 00:02:29,450
Brother...

54
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:31,010
Brother, why did you do this?

55
00:02:31,340 --> 00:02:32,850
I was just worried about you.

56
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:34,650
Why do you always...

57
00:02:34,740 --> 00:02:37,070
resort to violence when upset?

58
00:02:37,950 --> 00:02:39,270
Teacher Ai, what happened...?

59
00:02:39,270 --> 00:02:40,270
Get a towel first.
Yes!

60
00:02:41,260 --> 00:02:42,300
It's all right.

61
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:44,190
This is a family matter.

62
00:02:44,920 --> 00:02:47,610
He's been jealous of me since we were kids.

63
00:02:49,310 --> 00:02:50,170
But...

64
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:52,610
I've never hated my brother.

65
00:02:53,630 --> 00:02:54,520
Today

66
00:02:54,540 --> 00:02:56,130
I only came to congratulate him.

67
00:02:58,690 --> 00:03:00,200
Even if it's a family business

68
00:03:00,380 --> 00:03:01,640
it's still violence.

69
00:03:01,850 --> 00:03:02,760
Teacher.

70
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:04,760
I'm sorry, I must call the police...

71
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,190
Please wait.

72
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:07,630
There must be a misunderstanding

73
00:03:07,630 --> 00:03:08,530
I did it.

74
00:03:11,730 --> 00:03:12,580
No.

75
00:03:13,830 --> 00:03:14,820
Correction. I'm about to do it now.

76
00:03:20,830 --> 00:03:21,530
Teacher.

77
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:25,280
Since I'll be blamed anyway.

78
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:27,460
Might as well actually do it.

79
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:30,010
What do you mean?

80
00:03:34,660 --> 00:03:35,750
You know what this is?

81
00:03:36,910 --> 00:03:37,700
Huh?

82
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:40,640
Acting like you're having breakdown?

83
00:03:44,850 --> 00:03:45,810
I agree.

84
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:48,700
What? Are you grabbing my hand
and force me to splash you?

85
00:03:49,050 --> 00:03:49,690
Stop.

86
00:03:49,690 --> 00:03:53,490
No~ This way...

87
00:03:53,550 --> 00:03:54,960
- is much simpler.
- Stop it!

88
00:03:58,060 --> 00:03:58,940
It's not like that.

89
00:03:59,260 --> 00:03:59,810
Ah.
This is...

90
00:04:00,930 --> 00:04:02,380
I've been framed.

91
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:04,630
Let me teach you one more thing.

92
00:04:15,230 --> 00:04:16,510
Use your brain.

93
00:04:32,370 --> 00:04:33,830
Is everything settled?

94
00:04:34,310 --> 00:04:35,060
Yeah.

95
00:04:35,410 --> 00:04:36,350
It was exhausting though.

96
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,460
Good boy.

97
00:04:43,390 --> 00:04:44,750
You're so clever.

98
00:04:45,750 --> 00:04:46,620
Really.

99
00:04:48,940 --> 00:04:49,650
Earlier.

100
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:51,840
I met Ai-san's cousin.

101
00:04:52,860 --> 00:04:53,620
Huh?

102
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:56,280
She said she wanted to buy me.

103
00:04:58,140 --> 00:05:01,700
I thought if I accepted,
I might learn her true intentions.

104
00:05:02,550 --> 00:05:04,550
But I don't want to deceive you,
not even for a second.

105
00:05:04,910 --> 00:05:05,830
So I turned her down.

106
00:05:07,110 --> 00:05:07,820
I'm sorry.

107
00:05:10,590 --> 00:05:12,330
Knowing that is enough.

108
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:15,130
Next

109
00:05:15,710 --> 00:05:16,400
we'll use this.

110
00:05:17,190 --> 00:05:18,010
To stab someone?

111
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:21,560
Of course not.

112
00:05:22,180 --> 00:05:24,800
This recorder pen was a birthday gift from Himeka.

113
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:26,130
For self-defense.

114
00:05:27,370 --> 00:05:28,600
Self-defense...

115
00:05:30,230 --> 00:05:31,490
While protecting ourselves

116
00:05:35,870 --> 00:05:37,690
expose the real conspiracy.

117
00:06:13,300 --> 00:06:19,700
Love Sea: The Home for Lovers
(Episode 8)

118
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:24,660
Thank you.

119
00:06:24,670 --> 00:06:26,610
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much.

120
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:32,200
Please! I'm a huge fan! Ever since the yakuza series.

121
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:33,610
Wow.

122
00:06:34,090 --> 00:06:35,500
- Since that early?
- Yes.

123
00:06:35,530 --> 00:06:36,740
Thank you.

124
00:06:38,910 --> 00:06:40,080
Which character is your favorite?

125
00:06:40,190 --> 00:06:43,080
The main characterâ€”the cowardly, shameless handsome guy.

126
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:44,910
What a joy!

127
00:06:45,770 --> 00:06:46,580
There you go.

128
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,440
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

129
00:06:49,140 --> 00:06:49,820
My name is Yuri.
Nice to meet you, Yuri.

130
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:53,880
Teacher Beppu.

131
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:56,660
Your signing event tomorrow is cancelled.

132
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:58,770
Why?

133
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:00,520
You're asking why?

134
00:07:03,690 --> 00:07:04,550
Who is this?

135
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:09,000
[Link to a disturbing video]
(Message: Too much. Rin pissed?)

136
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:08,500
(Is this a joke?)

137
00:07:10,940 --> 00:07:11,880
This way...

138
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:13,440
is... much simpler.

139
00:07:13,570 --> 00:07:14,500
What...

140
00:07:21,820 --> 00:07:23,660
How did this get leaked?

141
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,840
One of you must have done it.

142
00:07:32,170 --> 00:07:33,010
Huh?
(Message: Terrible, explain this)
(Message: Forget it, no point, let's break up!)

143
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:36,450
You've got to be kidding me.

144
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,320
Give back my 50 million!!

145
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:43,820
What a shame.

146
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:48,170
- Too bad I missed all the fun.
- Not fun at all.

147
00:07:48,470 --> 00:07:50,390
Media inquiries are flooding in.

148
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:52,770
And on top of that, so is this...

149
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:54,370
This?

150
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:56,460
After all

151
00:07:56,950 --> 00:07:58,860
it's too hard for an amateur.

152
00:07:59,190 --> 00:08:01,060
Using someone like me for practice.

153
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:02,500
That's because Fumi said...

154
00:08:02,590 --> 00:08:05,020
to be grateful for the recorder pen.

155
00:08:05,710 --> 00:08:06,650
Well...

156
00:08:07,070 --> 00:08:09,910
- I just said to show gratitude...
- It's fine.

157
00:08:10,150 --> 00:08:11,910
It's easier than changing a lightbulb, isn't it?

158
00:08:13,370 --> 00:08:14,600
No way...

159
00:08:21,420 --> 00:08:23,550
I can't teach you If you run away.

160
00:08:30,450 --> 00:08:31,270
See

161
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:32,360
these are the stage directions.

162
00:08:32,760 --> 00:08:33,990
In other words, the actor's movements.

163
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:35,030
And

164
00:08:35,150 --> 00:08:36,210
these are the lines.

165
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,540
Take this for example

166
00:08:38,670 --> 00:08:40,110
there are about twenty scenes in total.

167
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:44,760
Eh, all of them?

168
00:08:44,830 --> 00:08:47,250
No, just practice the scenes with the two.

169
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:48,910
For instance.

170
00:08:49,530 --> 00:08:50,860
Hesitating.

171
00:08:51,690 --> 00:08:53,250
Gently approaching.

172
00:08:58,270 --> 00:08:59,810
Yuka grips her hand tightly.

173
00:09:02,090 --> 00:09:02,970
Honestly.

174
00:09:03,580 --> 00:09:04,970
Should I admit it?

175
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:08,650
To this love...

176
00:09:09,460 --> 00:09:11,520
I'm already deeply trapped.

177
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:15,740
Hold my hand back.

178
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:43,900
I'm still...

179
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:46,510
haven't memorized lines, I'm useless

180
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:49,670
I'll memorize them properly next time.

181
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:50,990
Good work.

182
00:10:01,540 --> 00:10:02,500
You, too.

183
00:10:02,710 --> 00:10:03,530
Are you going to bed?

184
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:09,270
Good night.

185
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:12,630
- Aren't you going to sleep?
- No, I'm also...

186
00:10:12,660 --> 00:10:13,610
Sleep in my bed.

187
00:10:14,160 --> 00:10:14,840
Huh?

188
00:10:16,530 --> 00:10:17,320
Can I?

189
00:10:24,030 --> 00:10:25,450
I really wanted to sleep though...

190
00:10:26,810 --> 00:10:27,820
Sorry.

191
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:30,030
Because it was so comfortable

192
00:10:32,050 --> 00:10:32,900
8 points.

193
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:34,120
Huh?

194
00:10:35,590 --> 00:10:36,670
You mean my bed skills?

195
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:37,800
No.

196
00:10:38,340 --> 00:10:39,310
It's your score

197
00:10:40,090 --> 00:10:40,900
8 points.

198
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:43,150
Out of 100.

199
00:10:44,770 --> 00:10:46,310
That's failing.

200
00:10:47,350 --> 00:10:48,540
Because I like the number 8.

201
00:10:53,310 --> 00:10:54,540
What's that about?

202
00:10:58,710 --> 00:10:59,530
Ai-san.

203
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:01,670
Something I want to show you.

204
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:14,970
Handmade crafts...?

205
00:11:15,610 --> 00:11:17,290
Made at the island workshop?

206
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:18,500
Yes.

207
00:11:19,060 --> 00:11:20,090
These are all...

208
00:11:20,340 --> 00:11:22,540
accessories made from recycled materials.

209
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:26,670
I co-own a shop with a Thai person.

210
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:31,950
I spent years balancing design and cost.

211
00:11:33,210 --> 00:11:34,640
We're finally ready to sell soon.

212
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:36,870
So cute.

213
00:11:37,490 --> 00:11:38,500
Girls would love these.

214
00:11:39,290 --> 00:11:40,260
What about you?

215
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:41,660
Do you like it?

216
00:11:45,450 --> 00:11:46,290
I do.

217
00:11:47,580 --> 00:11:48,440
Very cute.

218
00:11:51,130 --> 00:11:52,480
I also like Ai-san.

219
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:55,870
I meant the bracelet.

220
00:12:00,670 --> 00:12:01,120
I always...

221
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:02,800
wanted to live on that island...

222
00:12:03,430 --> 00:12:06,000
and develop eco-friendly tourism.

223
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,780
It's been my dream since before.

224
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:12,340
What about now?

225
00:12:14,050 --> 00:12:15,020
Now...

226
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:17,430
I'm kind of...

227
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:19,030
starting to feel confused.

228
00:12:22,230 --> 00:12:23,770
Because I have someone important.

229
00:12:23,830 --> 00:12:24,910
No need to be confused.

230
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:27,100
Huh?

231
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:33,240
Dreams should be fulfilled.

232
00:12:35,810 --> 00:12:37,480
Haven't you always worked for this?

233
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,410
I'm getting up early, going to sleep.

234
00:12:43,010 --> 00:12:43,620
Huh?

235
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:45,420
Where are you going tomorrow?

236
00:12:47,250 --> 00:12:48,840
None of your business.

237
00:12:54,090 --> 00:12:55,380
Are you going out today, too?

238
00:12:55,650 --> 00:12:56,480
Where are you going?

239
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:58,180
None of your business.

240
00:12:58,210 --> 00:12:59,200
Wait.

241
00:13:00,970 --> 00:13:02,410
Answer me before you leaving

242
00:13:04,380 --> 00:13:05,600
I'll say it again...

243
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:07,410
None of your business.

244
00:13:17,690 --> 00:13:19,560
Is this something appropriate to discuss with a kid?

245
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,870
Who else can I talk to?

246
00:13:22,820 --> 00:13:25,810
Having no friends is kind of a turn-off.

247
00:13:26,580 --> 00:13:27,050
Ah.

248
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:28,510
Maybe he's tired of you?

249
00:13:29,630 --> 00:13:30,720
Impossible.

250
00:13:31,420 --> 00:13:33,350
What makes you so confident?

251
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:36,250
Uncle Ai...

252
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:38,900
is charming and popular...

253
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,060
Any newcomer won't let him go.

254
00:13:41,790 --> 00:13:43,520
Even so, it's impossible.

255
00:13:44,550 --> 00:13:46,440
Kids might not understand.

256
00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:47,810
I'm also pretty...

257
00:13:48,220 --> 00:13:49,440
charming, you know.

258
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:55,710
You're only about ten years older than me.

259
00:13:56,500 --> 00:14:00,030
To Uncle Ai, you are like a kid.

260
00:14:00,760 --> 00:14:01,530
You're kidding me.

261
00:14:09,230 --> 00:14:10,110
There must be a mistake.

262
00:14:10,580 --> 00:14:12,560
It's a bit different...

263
00:14:15,070 --> 00:14:16,890
It's been so long.

264
00:14:18,010 --> 00:14:19,620
Long time no see.

265
00:14:20,770 --> 00:14:22,120
Good to know you're doing well.

266
00:14:23,230 --> 00:14:24,670
Uncle Shusaku.

267
00:14:27,670 --> 00:14:28,990
To be honest, right now

268
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:31,330
I'm troubled about your son.

269
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:37,000
I saw that video, even I barely go online.

270
00:14:38,530 --> 00:14:40,020
It must've been rough.

271
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:45,040
Thanks to him, my book publication almost got cancelled...

272
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:47,530
My mom also scolded me a lot.

273
00:14:49,230 --> 00:14:50,230
So...

274
00:14:50,590 --> 00:14:52,150
The reason I called today...

275
00:14:52,470 --> 00:14:54,120
is about those photos I sent you.

276
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:01,820
Everyone looks lovely.

277
00:15:02,820 --> 00:15:03,550
And...

278
00:15:04,110 --> 00:15:05,170
this man...

279
00:15:05,920 --> 00:15:08,310
is the one who picks up Mina.

280
00:15:09,230 --> 00:15:10,740
Is he a servant?

281
00:15:12,110 --> 00:15:13,000
No.

282
00:15:13,820 --> 00:15:15,590
He lives with Ai.

283
00:15:16,970 --> 00:15:18,530
Probably his lover.

284
00:15:19,230 --> 00:15:20,280
Suppose so...

285
00:15:21,550 --> 00:15:22,570
Oh.

286
00:15:25,730 --> 00:15:27,590
I'll get straight to the point.

287
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:30,330
I don't care how you do it.

288
00:15:31,330 --> 00:15:33,650
Please take away what's important to Ai...

289
00:15:33,890 --> 00:15:35,710
and make him despair.

290
00:15:38,870 --> 00:15:39,780
